For this assignment, I have implemented all required functionality and fixed multiple bugs that caused previously unknown issues. My character can successfully move between maps using the h,j,k, and l keys, I did not implment the diagonal keys for map traversal, as it caused undefined behavior and errors when dealing with multiple gates in a corner area. The fly function is implemented and requires the user to implement the coordinates in a x y manner with a space between x and y. Flying will place the player on a random piece of road on the selected map. Each map has seperate queues and characters, and are maintained in between maps. My code is updated to C++ and uses the class system and proper new/delete techniques rather than malloc/free as well as constructors and deconstructors.